  "summary": "Bobby meets with Moira Nicholson, who reveals herself to be the wife of Dr. Nicholson. Terrified and trembling, Moira confesses her belief that her husband intends to murder her. She cites several \"accidents\" as evidence of his intent, including a near-miss with a vehicle and the discovery of medications that had been mixed up in their bottles. Moira claims Dr. Nicholson's motive is his infatuation with Sylvia Baxton-French. She suspects the doctor is attempting to have Sylvia's husband, Henry Baxton-French, committed to Granchester Sanatorium. Moira describes the sanatorium as a sinister place where patients' conditions deteriorate rather than improve.\n\nMoira believes a man named Jasper is manipulating both Henry—who is a morphine user—and his brother, Roger, to facilitate Henry's move to the sanatorium. She expresses doubt regarding Sylvia's true nature, wondering if the woman is merely acting. When Bobby asks if she knows Allen Castles, Moira admits she knew him before her marriage; he visited her approximately one month ago, though she did not provide him with her location. She has not disclosed her fears or her unhappy marriage to Castles. Finally, Moira describes her husband as an extremely strange and jealous man who views her as his property.",
